  "texts": [
    "Addressing ethical considerations and validation challengesWhile AI-powered 4D ultrasound offers remarkable potential, several ethical and practical challenges must be addressed to ensure safe and equitable deployment.",
    "One major concern involves algorithmic bias, which can arise when AI models are trained on non-representative datasets [53].",
    "Such biases may result in diagnostic inaccuracies, particularly for underrepresented populations [46].",
    "Ensuring dataset diversity and conducting external validations across different demographics are crucial to mitigating this risk [44].Transparency and interpretability of AI models are equally important, as clinicians need clear explanations of how diagnostic predictions are generated [45].",
    "This transparency fosters trust and supports informed decisionmaking [45]."
  ],
